    <summary>Bambu Farm Manager Client is the desktop dashboard for monitoring and controlling a local fleet of Bambu printers via the Farm Manager Server, with live status, queue management, and batch actions for print-farm workflows.</summary>
    <description><![CDATA[
Bambu Farm Manager Client is the GUI for the Farm Manager suite. It connects to your local Farm Manager Server to provide real-time monitoring, queue control, and convenient batch actions for multi-printer environments.

### Features
- Live dashboard with printer status, progress, and alerts
- Centralized queue and job management (send, reorder, pause/resume, cancel)
- Batch operations across multiple devices
- Local-first workflow after initial activation (no ongoing cloud dependency)
- Ideal for print farms, classrooms, and labs

### What this package does
- Installs the **Farm Manager Client** for Windows using the official installer (silent "/S")
- Suitable for unattended/automated deployments and AU-based updates

### Compatibility and requirements
- Windows 10/11 (per vendor support)
- Network access to the Farm Manager Server on the same LAN

### Post-install verification
- Launch “Farm Manager Client”, connect to your Farm Manager Server, and verify printers are visible with up-to-date status.

